Abstract = {With the rapid development of artificial intelligence, big data, cloud
   computing, and other technologies, supporting digital twin technology
   has become a research hotspot today. It expounds the modeling and
   application of digital twins in the field of smart cities, and studies
   the network in digital twin cities. The optimization model, in view of
   the diversity and burstiness of the traffic in the network, in order to
   effectively handle the increasing user access data traffic and the
   increasingly wide range of business types, a dynamic traffic scheduling
   method based on the swarm intelligence optimization algorithm is
   designed, and a gray-based dynamic traffic scheduling method is
   proposed. Intelligent path planning algorithm optimized by wolf. The
   simulation shows that for different types of services, the algorithm can
   set different priorities based on delay/bandwidth, calculate the optimal
   path, suboptimal alternate path, third alternate path, and realize
   intelligent obstacle avoidance and intelligent decision-making.
   Scheduling, so as to carry out efficient, reasonable and intelligent
   traffic scheduling. And in the case of a node failure on the optimal
   path, the optimal path based on the shortest distance can be quickly
   calculated.},
